OL,3,CCouncil tax burden almost doubles for
OL,4,Cpoorest households
OL,6,FThis includes extra funding to offset
OL,7,Frising employer National Insurance
OL,8,Fcosts. But this is only for staff
OL,9,Femployed by councils, so the costs for
OL,10,Fcontracted services will likely rise.
OL,11,FThis could impact areas like social
OL,12,Fcare.
OL,14,FResearch by the Institute for
OL,15,FGovernment for the ITV Peston
OL,16,FProgramme shows how spending power has
OL,17,Fgrown in the most deprived areas. This
OL,18,Fhas been achieved through a fund
OL,19,Fcalled the Recovery Grant. But this
OL,20,Fmeans spending power will not rise at
OL,21,Fthe same rate for rural areas.
